	Google Java Style Guide

	Google Java Style Guide link: https://google.github.io/styleguide/javaguide.html

1)	Import code style file

1.1)	Download 'intellij-java-google-style.xml' file
	
	https://github.com/google/styleguide/blob/gh-pages/intellij-java-google-style.xml

1.2)	Setting

	File >> Setting (or Ctrl+Alt+S) >> Editor >> Code Style >> Java >> Scheme >> Show Scheme Actions >>
	>> Import Scheme >> IntelliJ IDEA code style xml >> select 'intellij-java-google-style.xml'

1.3)	Using

	Code > Reformat Code (or Ctrl+Alt+L)


2)	or install 'google-java-format' plugin

2.1)	Open plugins window: File >> Setting >> Plugins (or CTRL+Shift+A)

2.2)	Search for 'google-java-format'

2.3)	Install plugin and restart IDE

2.4)	Enable plugin executing action: Reformat with google-java-format (or Ctrl+Shift+A)
